  "text": "From a treatment point of view, interest has specifically been given to the use of dental implants. Yap and Klineberg [CITATION_1] stated that the success rate is lower for implants in patients with ectodermal dysplasia than it is in patients with tooth agenesis but without ectodermal dysplasia.",
